milestones.description: Fleming and Nathan Astle's 193-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 158 between John Wright and Martin Crowe
Nathan Astle has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (84) in an innings in ODIs for NZ, going past Glenn Turner's 76
Fleming and Nathan Astle's 193-run partnership is NZ's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 180 between Adam Parore and Rutherford

stories.title: ICC Match Referee Ranjan Madugalle confirms reporting of Shoaib Akhtar
stories.summary: Umpires Doug Cowie and Steve Dunne, who officiated in yesterday's One Day International match in Dunedin between New Zealand and Pakistan, have reported Pakistan fast bowler Shoaib Akhtar for a suspect bowling action

stories.title: Astle rates century one of his best
stories.summary: New Zealand's man of the match Nathan Astle in last night's win over Pakistan rated his 119 one of the best of his nine One-Day International centuries

stories.title: Top order makes life a whole lot easier for winning Kiwis
stories.summary: New Zealand's top order came good at the right time to end the long haul of 27 One-Day Internationals this summer with a series win over Pakistan

stories.title: Astle and Fleming set up fine win for New Zealand to clinch series
stories.summary: A record-breaking all wickets partnership of 193 runs by Nathan Astle and Stephen Fleming set New Zealand up for a thrilling National Bank series win over Pakistan in Dunedin today
